    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                                         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Shine}Welcome to @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 5th issue of @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.

The  same  mistakes, the same consequences. At @{B}WoA@{UB}, @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} almost killed the
@{B}Amiga  Classic@{UB}.  Sure,  their  plans for the future are cool, but they forgot to
support  the  current  line  of  @{B}Amiga@{UB}s taking into account that Next Generation
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  won't  be  ready  until  the  end  of 1999. Probably you already know the
consequences  of  this  decision:  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  market  shrunk to minimal levels,
magazines  and  companies  gone  out  of  business  ,and  software projects were
canceled.

Then,  it seemed they realized their mistakes and they announced the development
of  the  @{B}OS  3.5@{UB}  at  @{B}MAE@{UB} in Ohio last month. Actually, the responsible for this
change was @{I}Fleecy Moss@{UI}.

@{I}Fleecy@{UI}  is  British and he's a project manager and systems architect responsible
for  implementing entreprise level distributed computing systems. He has been an
@{B}Amiga@{UB} user for about 8 years, and started out on a @{B}Commodore Pet@{UB} and @{B}Vic 20@{UB} when
he was about 11. And he still has to finnish @{B}Cannon Fodder@{UB}.

After  the  @{B}Computer'98@{UB},  our "friend" @{I}Jeff@{UI} seems to revert to his old ways. And
now,  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  has been oficially killed by the parent company because @{I}Fleecy@{UI}
has  been  sacked.  Now, it is uncertain if the @{B}Amiga OS 3.5@{UB} will be released or
not.

As  I'm  against  all the conspiracy theories, I think that this only means that
@{B}Amiga  Inc.@{UB}  has  no  interest in the current line of @{B}Amiga@{UB}s. So they don't care
about  us. And I don't care about them. I hope they will succeed in bringing its
revolutionary  operating  system,  but  if  the fail I won't be worried. This is
their problem, not mine.

Unlike many others this magazine will be released each month as usual. At least,
while there is an @{B}Amiga@{UB} turned on in the world.

They have the Intelectual Propierty, but nor the community nor its philosophy.

Remember to visit the @{B}SAUG@{UB} website, which is located in:

         @{B}http://www.saug.com/@{UB}

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

         @{B}http://soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/@{UB}

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
@{I}Angel Alvarez Díaz @{UI} - @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}
Member of @{B}C.U.A.E@{UB} Nº 293 - @{I}FOREIGN DIRECTOR @{UI}
Responsible of the News Departament of @{B}S.A.U.@{UB} and @{B}Amiga Channel@{UB}.
