@node not04 "THE LAST PATRIOT: THE FIRST GAME PLANNED FOR THE OS5PROD MACHINES"

@{B}THE LAST PATRIOT@{UB}: THE FIRST GAME PLANNED FOR THE @{B}OS5PROD@{UB} MACHINES
-----------------------------------------------------------------

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

@{B}Delsyd  Software@{UB}  would  like  to announce the development of a new game for the
@{B}Amiga@{UB}---@{B}The  Last  Patriot@{UB}.  After  7 months of planning and design work, we are
ready  to  get  going.  @{B}The  Last Patriot@{UB} will be a puzzle-oriented first-person
perspective  shooter. Instead of just mindless running and shooting, you'll have
to  think  before you act, and we don't mean flipping switches, either. @{B}The Last
Patriot@{UB}  will  feature  the most advanced artificial intelligence EVER seen in a
video  game.  Each  enemy  will  have  their  own  very basic thought processes,
instincts, and personalities. We are shooting for a March 2000 release date, and
it  will  be released for the @{B}NG Amiga@{UB}. This date could get pushed back some due
to  development system/@{B}Amiga NG@{UB} delays. We're putting all of our money into this
project, and we think you'll enjoy the end product.

@{B}PPC@{UB}  versions  are  being  considered.  We would like to hear some feedback from
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  gamers. If you have any questions or ideas concerning @{B}The Last Patriot@{UB} or
@{B}Delsyd Software@{UB}, we can be reached at @{I}delsydsoftware@yahoo.com@{UI}

We  would  also  like to announce the October issue of @{B}Amiga Issues@{UB}, our monthly
forum  that  deals  with  some  of  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s more controversial issues. This
month's  topic involves @{B}Vulcan Software@{UB} and their recent software cancellations.
@{B}Amiga Issues@{UB} also contains "The Software Accelerator's Corner", where each month
we review a new patch or software tweak to keep your @{B}Amiga@{UB} moving. And, there is
also  a  section  dedicated  to  responses  that our readers have sent us. We'll
include  any  letter  that you send to @{B}Amiga Issues@{UB}, even if we don't agree with
your opinion.

All    of    this    information   can   be   found   on   our   web   page   at
@{B}www.geocities.com/siliconvalley/foothills/2705/index.html@{UB}

We hope to hear from you very soon. See ya!
@{I}Chris Kelley@{UI}
Head Programmer/@{B}Delsyd Software@{UB}
