System@{UB},  @{B}Quake@{UB},  @{B}Big  Red  Adventure@{UB}, @{B}Virtual Karting 2@{UB}, A-Z of @{B}Amiga@{UB} games, and
@{B}Shadow of the Third Moon@{UB}. Phew!

@{B}The Informer@{UB} magazine is also happy to announce that it is now being distributed
in  the  UK  and  other  European  countries.  @{B}Amiga  Survivor@{UB}  distribution  is
dispersing  @{B}The Informer@{UB} to shops throughout The UK, Sweden and other countries.
You  can  visit  them  at @{B}www.crystal-software.com/AmigaSurvivor/survindex.html@{UB}.
Inquires  can be emailed to @{I}robert@survivor.enterprise-plc.com@{UI}. One of the first
big  retailers  of  @{B}The  Informer@{UB}  in  England is @{B}Epic Marketing@{UB} and they can be
reached at @{B}www.epicmarketing.ltd.net@{UB}.

Our  website  (@{B}www.amigainformer.com@{UB})  was  recently  updated with articles that
appeared in recently past issues of @{B}The Informer@{UB}. Browse through these to get an
idea of what we are all about and to learn a few things in the process.

So,  if  you  want  to  get  a fresh view of what's going on in the world of the
@{B}Amiga@{UB},  get  a  copy of issue 16. The best way of doing that is to call our toll
free number (800-882-6442) and subscribe. You'll be glad you did.

Cheers,

