@node not07 "CANDYFACTORY PRO TO BE RELEASED AT COMPUTER' 98"

@{B}CANDYFACTORY PRO@{UB} TO BE RELEASED AT @{B}COMPUTER' 98@{UB}
-----------------------------------------------

@{I}Milan  Polle@{UI}  is  working  hard  on  finishing @{B}Candy Factory Pro@{UB}, the commercial
successor  to @{B}Candy Factory 0.54b@{UB}. It will be available at the @{B}Computer '98@{UB} fair
in Cologne November 13, 14, 15, from @{B}Titan Computer@{UB}/@{B}MotionStudios@{UB}.

Some of the new additions are:
  * Major speedups, upto 18 times, for most effects
  * Realtime  24bit support, apply all effects with realtime 24bit (or truecolor
    8bit dither on @{B}AGA@{UB}) shading.
  * Color  texturing,  add  an  image  as  a color pattern/reflection map to the
    object or background, with realtime truecolor moving/sizing.
  * Bumpmapping,  use  the  standard  noisebumps or a custom image as a bumpmap.
    Totally   rewritten  routines  giving  better  quality.  Realtime  truecolor
    adjusting.
  * Environment  mapping,  use the standard metallic effect or a custom image as
    an environment map. Realtime truecolor positioning/distance.
  * Add  antialiased  text, using @{B}CG@{UB} fonts, with rotation, emboldening, hearing,
    etc.
  * High  quality  render  passes  interpolate/supersample textures, bumpmaps or
    environment maps, removing blockiness.
  * High quality shading pass gives smooth truecolor shading and highlights.
  * Save alpha channel transparancy information to an image file.
  * Save  settings, save window configuration, realtime prefs, filepath settings
    and change the screenmode on the fly.
  * Multiple loaders/savers by @{B}MotionStudios@{UB} (@{B}Elastic Dreams@{UB}).
  * as well as various bugfixes and other enhancements.

For    more   information,   visit   @{I}Robert   Nyberg@{UI}'s   @{B}CandyFactory@{UB}   Central:
@{B}http://www.grafik.nu/candy/@{UB}
