system for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}!@{UI}

@{I}Summary of Enhancements@{UI}

The @{B}Magellan-II@{UB} version not only upgrades many of the earlier functions but also
involves  an extensive re-development of many components of the @{B}Opus 5@{UB} system to
give  you  enhanced  usability,  especially  in  the @{B}Workbench@{UB} Replacement Mode.
Amongst  other  features,  in  this  version  we  have concentrated on providing
greater  user  control  over  your  custom  @{I}Environment@{UI} with a more powerful but
easier  to  use  configuration  section,  plus  many new features such as custom
@{I}Themes@{UI}, custom sounds and scripts, improved @{I}User@{UI} and @{I}Start Menus@{UI}, greater @{I}Lister@{UI}
functionality,  and  a  dramatically  enhanced  @{I}OpusFTP@{UI} system where you can now
tailor custom setting for individual remote sites and even leave out the site or
remote files on your @{B}Opus@{UB} desktop for instant access.

Amongst many other features, the @{B}Magellan@{UB} version gave you:-
  * Enhanced  @{I}Lister@{UI}  functionality  including:-  command functions which act on
    icon  mode @{I}Listers@{UI}; new popup menus; optional @{I}Space Gauge@{UI} showing free space
    on  drives, @{I}Inline Editing@{UI} for @{I}Name@{UI} mode @{I}Listers@{UI} and the ability to drag and
    drop files directly into sub-directories.
  * A new integrated system of @{I}Start Menus@{UI}.
  * A  new @{I}Desktop Folder@{UI} mechanism: @{I}Drag and drop@{UI} items to the desktop with the
    support of optional popup menus.
  * A  new  @{I}Icon Positioning@{UI} system. Configure areas where icons will appear and
    their priority.
  * Improved  @{I}Icon@{UI}  dragging  routines  plus  global  control of icon labels and
    borders;  icon  label splitting for long labels; a new @{I}Icon Command@{UI} function
    for  special  "command"  files; and the ability to use traditional @{B}Workbench@{UB}
    icon positions for icons or exclusive @{B}Opus@{UB} positioning.
  * New @{I}Popup@{UI} menus with shadow look.
  * Integrated  @{B}NewIcons@{UB}  support  not  just for icons but for all system images
    including  graphic  button  banks  plus support for image and animation file
    formats including @{B}DPaintV@{UB}/@{B}PPaint AnimBrushes@{UB}.

The  new @{B}Magellan-II@{UB} version refines and extends these features further. The new
features include:-
  * Custom  @{I}Themes@{UI}  -  customise your system with your favourite images, sounds,
    fonts and colours.
  * Improved @{I}Lister@{UI} layouts including proportional fonts, resizable fields, sort
    indicator, better in-line editing.
  * An  amalgamated  @{B}Options@{UB} and @{B}Environment@{UB} editor to give you a more intuitive
    layout for better management of the display and program operations.
  * Background pictures in button banks and start menus.
  * Random Background images.
  * New @{I}Outline@{UI} and @{I}Shadow@{UI} font options for @{B}Workbench@{UB} display.
  * Fully  user  configurable  screen  title  for  display of used and available
    memory, @{B}OS@{UB} versions, processes etc.
  * New  @{I}Sound@{UI}  events  for @{B}Opus@{UB} and system events - attach a sound to inserting
    and removing a disk! Use Random Sounds
  * New  @{B}Opus@{UB} @{I}Path List@{UI} settings allowing you to easily set the system paths for
    commands etc.
  * Support for @{B}Filesystems@{UB} with filenames up to 107 characters.
  * New  graphical  layout  and better configurability of @{I}Button@{UI} banks and start
    menus including an 'auto-close' feature. Buttons now support "Active Popups"
    - an extended popup menu feature where each button act as a start menu.
  * Revised  internal commands with many now replaceable by user-defined scripts
    and functions.
  * Enhanced  Scripts  system  with more events and linking to internal commands
    and @{I}OpusFTP@{UI}.
  * Improved  @{I}Start Menus@{UI}. You can now have multilevel menus and start menus are
    now always 'sticky'
  * Improved  filetype identification system with better control of multitasking
    for  large  directories and CDs and new filetype matching functions to match
    foreign disk types.
  * New and extended icon and Lister popup menus.
  * Improved @{I}Snapshot@{UI} ability for @{I}Listers@{UI}, @{I}Icon@{UI} modes and @{I}Groups@{UI}.
  * New   @{I}Icon  Information@{UI}  requester  with  more  detailed  display  plus  new
    functionality such as ability to change icon type and edit the icon images.
  * Improved support for @{I}Drag and Drop@{UI} functions.
  * Better @{B}Icon@{UB} support with faster displays.
  * Many new @{B}ARexx@{UB} commands to control @{B}Opus@{UB}.

This  functionality  is  complemented  by a dramatically enhanced @{I}OpusFTP@{UI} module
with many new features including:-
