@node not22 "MAXON COMPUTERS STOP ALL DEVELOPMENT CONCERNING THE AMIGA"

@{B}MAXON COMPUTERS@{UB} STOP ALL DEVELOPMENT CONCERNING THE @{B}AMIGA@{UB}
---------------------------------------------------------

Dear @{B}Amiga@{UB}-Users,

Since  the  middle  of  the  ninetees  there have been hot discussions about the
future of the @{B}AMIGA@{UB}.

Unfortunately  a  lot of them turned out to be nothing but hot air - mostly good
ideas with no functioning concepts.

Even  if  there  were  some  moments  of  hope in the last few years, all of the
development turned out to be more complex in reality than it was planned. So the
economical needs forced us to make some decisions.

We had to decide to stop all further activities concerning the @{B}AMIGA@{UB}.

At  the  last  trade shows we have often answered the question for a port to the
@{B}PowerUP@{UB}-Platform  with  "As  soon  as we get suitable developing-tools." - These
tools  still  aren't available. For an application as complex as @{B}CINEMA4D@{UB}, these
tools  are  totally  essential.  Without an object-oriented programming language
like @{B}C++@{UB} a useful port is not possible - the existing hardware is already at its
limits with the available version 4.

As  a company involved with the @{B}AMIGA@{UB} since 1986, which has been a market-leader
in  raytracing-software,  and  which  has produced a lot of books as well as the
German "@{B}Kickstart@{UB}"-magazine for the @{B}AMIGA@{UB}-market, it is even more hard to make a
decision.

Actually  the  last few results of the @{B}AMIGA@{UB} events in London and Toronto showed
that  there  will  be no general improvement of the situation in the next years.
Too  much  decisions took too much time, wrong decisions lead into dead ends and
too many parties acted uncoordinated.

Making  Plans  is  a  great thing - but in such a fast-changing economy like the
computer-business 2 years are a very long time - too long.

A  market  that  only  sells  a  few units a year makes it difficult to maintain
profitable,  which  is  absolute  must for a company that has to take social and
financial care about its staff and employees.

So  we  had  to  change  our  plans  and  @{B}CINEMA  4D@{UB}  has  concentrated  on  the
high-end-market  in  the  last  years,  where it has reached a safe top-position
worldwide.  Today  a  lot  of  big  TV-stations and production-studios are using
@{B}CINEMA  4D@{UB} and it's getting constantly the best marks and the most wanted awards
(e.g.  @{B}Siggraph  1997@{UB}  - "Best Animation-Tool: @{B}CINEMA 4D XL@{UB}"). And as we want to
fulfill  the  needs  of  this  market  in  the  future,  this  means  continuous
development.

We say goodbye and send out best wishes to you for the future.

Your

@{B}MAXON Computer GmbH@{UB}
