@node not27 "VULCAN CLOSES THE AMIGA DEVELOPMENT AFTER 5 YEARS OF EXISTANCE"

@{B}VULCAN@{UB} CLOSES THE @{B}AMIGA@{UB} DEVELOPMENT AFTER 5 YEARS OF EXISTANCE
--------------------------------------------------------------

@{I}GOODBYE @{B}AMIGA@{UB} CLASSIC@{UI}

@{B}Vulcan@{UB}  is finally closing the lid on @{B}Amiga@{UB} (classic) software development after
half  a  decade  of  support!  The  decision to leave comes close to @{B}Vulcan@{UB}s 5th
anniversary.

@{I}Paul  Carrington@{UI}  states  @{I}"...after  much deliberation we switched off our @{B}Amiga@{UB}
development  systems  at  the mains, quickly wrapped them in brown paper and hid
them  in  the  @{B}Vulcan@{UB} vault! It's quite sad to see these babies being turned off
but it is something we all knew was inevitable (and perhaps long overdue)."@{UI}

Since 1994 @{B}Vulcan@{UB} has Developed and Published 10 @{B}Amiga@{UB} floppy titles and 5 @{B}Amiga@{UB}
CDRom titles and currently has 2 more @{B}Amiga@{UB} CDRom titles still in production and
nearing release.

@{I}"I  hope  that  our departure from @{B}Amiga@{UB} (classic) software development does not
receive  the  same  insulting  and  slanderous  response  as  previous departing
companies  had experienced, but our decision is based purely on a commercial and
financial  level  due to the current state of the existing @{B}Amiga@{UB} market. To show
our loyalty to the platform (which was responsible for our companies success) we
will  remain  as  an  active  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  Publisher  as  long  as  there are external
developers  out there creating exciting products and require our services and as
long  as our @{B}Amiga@{UB} distributor still has an outlet to sell limited quantities of
@{B}Amiga@{UB} titles."@{UI}

@{B}Vulcan@{UB}  has  just  released  a  limited  edition @{B}Amiga@{UB} compilation CDRom of it's
MiniSeries  titles  as a tribute to it's golden days and we can still expect the
Alien  adventure  @{B}'Wasted Dreams' Amiga@{UB} CDRom to be released before Xmas 98 with
@{B}Explorer2260 Amiga PPC@{UB} CDRom scheduled for early 99.

Live Long & Prosper!

