@node  not33 "WARP3D AND STORMMESA TO BE PRESENTED AT THE HAAGE&PARTNER BOOTH AT
COLOGNE"

@{B}WARP3D@{UB} AND @{B}STORMMESA@{UB} TO BE PRESENTED AT THE @{B}HAAGE&PARTNER@{UB} BOOTH AT COLOGNE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The  @{B}Computer  '98@{UB}  in Cologne will see the first public presentation of @{B}Warp3D@{UB}.
The  hardware used will be the @{B}CyberVision3D@{UB}, showing off what the comparatively
weak @{B}ViRGE@{UB} chip is capable of doing, and it will become obvious that the rumours
are  wrong:  That the @{B}ViRGE@{UB} is not suited for fast 3D graphics. You will be able
to  see  quite  a  number  of  impressive  demos to show the possibilities of 3D
Hardware.

The  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}/@{B}WarpUp@{UB}-Conversion  will  also be in beta state and will be shown at
the  fair.  The  combination  of  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}  and 3D-Chips will result in an as yet
unseen performance in 3D computer graphics on the @{B}Amiga@{UB} sector.

As  a  second  highliht in the 3D realm will be the presentation of the graphics
library  @{B}StormMesa  3.0@{UB}.  This  library implements the @{B}OpenGL@{UB} API, and will be a
powerful  tool  for the development of 3D software. Version 3.0 will come in the
form of shared libraries for both types of CPU (@{B}68k@{UB}, @{B}PPC@{UB}).

Usually  @{B}OpenGL@{UB}-Software  requires very powerful hardware. Because of this, good
performance  can  only  be  achieved  if  all  system components work flawlessly
together.  For the first time in Cologne you will be able to see the combination
of  @{B}OpenGL@{UB}  and  3D  Hardware for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. @{B}StormMesa 3.0@{UB} will contain a driver
that  uses  the  @{B}Warp3D@{UB}-APU  and thus redirects 3D rendering to the 3D hardware.
This  will  finally  set the stage for porting e.g. @{B}OpenGL@{UB}-supporting games from
other platforms with a minimal effort in time and money.

We  invite  you to visit our booth and to see for yourself what it means to have
top  software and top hardware working together. See the combination of @{B}PowerPC@{UB},
3D-Hardware,  @{B}WarpOS@{UB}, @{B}Warp3D@{UB} and @{B}OpenGL@{UB}/@{B}StormMesa@{UB}, and see the @{B}Amiga@{UB} turned into
a top machine again.

More info on the "3D-World" page of @{B}Haage&Partner@{UB}.
@{B}http://www.haage-partner.com/3DWorld/index_eng.html@{UB}
