@node art03 "COLOGNE / SOBER ANALYSIS OF THE SOBER ANALYSIS BY MARTIN HEINE"

COLOGNE / SOBER ANALYSIS OF THE SOBER ANALYSIS BY @{I}MARTIN HEINE@{UI}
--------------------------------------------------------------

Well, I've been there - and I really don't regret it!!!

Since  still  nobody  else  did,  I'll  give  you  a  few  infos about the press
conference  -  but  there's  no warranty all I'll mention is correct, especially
because the conference was not held in my native language.

(Btw:  Since  I'll  have  to  write  this  quick,  the  result  will be horrible
German-English;  but  I  think  you'll understand it anyway and since there's no
other report yet in this NG this seems to be better than nothing.)

Already  just  from  having  met  the  people  of  @{B}AI@{UB}  and  the  one  of the two
@{B}QNX@{UB}-presidents who was there as well has reassured me. I'm quite certain we will
get what we want.

The  conference  was delayed. It was planned to make one exclusive first for the
press,  later the one for the public. But because of technical problems with the
demonstration - at least I suppose this was the reason - this delayed. Therefore
we were waiting before the room.

@{I}Bill@{UI}  came  out,  said that it would be delayed, thanked us for our interest and
patience  and  said in return to the delay he would let come some drinks for us:
@{I}"Is this okay?"@{UI} - Well, we didn't refused very much to accept this... =)

Some  time  later  he came again, said that it would delay a little bit more. He
told  us  that  it  was  originally  planned  to  have  that  separate exclusive
press-conference  first,  than  the  one for the public. So we sighed, expecting
that  we  would  have to wait even longer. But unexpectedly @{I}Bill@{UI} offered that we
could combine them, making just one conference for all, because of the delay. He
asked  us  just  to  leave  the first rows of seats in the room for the press. -
Well,  when  the  doors  finally  opened  some  minute  later,  and the crowd of
@{B}Amiga@{UB}-Fanatics  stormed  into  the room, the @{I}"let first the press into the room"@{UI}
was no longer valid... :)

At  the  conference were @{I}Jeff@{UI}, @{I}Allan@{UI}, @{I}Bill@{UI} and @{I}Darreck@{UI} of @{B}AI@{UB} and of course @{I}Petro@{UI}
of  @{B}AII@{UB}.  Additional  there  was  one  of  the two presidents of @{B}QNX@{UB}, but in the
beginning he was sitting in the auditorium.

In  the auditorium was also someone from the german TV-channel @{B}ZDF@{UB}. Therefore we
can  expect  that  the  big  news  of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}-@{B}QNX@{UB}-cooperation will be reported
correctly by them.

At  first  @{I}Petro@{UI} was speaking. The only new thing was that he confirmed that @{B}AII@{UB}
will  build  further  @{B}A4000T@{UB}  using the parts from @{B}Quikpak@{UB}, Mr. @{I}Hembach@{UI} gave his
okay.  @{I}Petro@{UI} said Mr. @{I}Hembach@{UI} would be a nice guy, but the auditorium made clear
it  thought different about him... :) The @{B}Amiga@{UB}-parts from @{B}Quikpak@{UB} are currently
shipping on the ocean, he told us.

Then @{I}Bill@{UI} spoke some introducing sentences and gave the word to @{I}Jeff@{UI}, than spoke
@{I}Allan@{UI}. Some details about @{B}OS3.5@{UB} and @{B}OS5@{UB} were told, but nothing really new.

And  then the big news - the OS-Kernel-partner is @{B}QNX@{UB}. A murmur went through the
auditorium,  many  were disappointed in the beginning, because they did not know
@{B}QNX@{UB}  and  had  expected  a  better  known  company like @{B}Be@{UB} or @{B}Sun@{UB}. But after the
demonstrations  they  were  certainly all as convinced as I that @{B}QNX@{UB} is the best
possible choice. Although it was already said in this NG that @{B}QNX@{UB} is the partner
and  that  their  homepage  is  @{B}www.qnx.com@{UB},  nobody  told you that they are big
Amigans!  Many  of  their  (IMHO  16)  developers  have  an @{B}Amiga@{UB}, and this even
includes  both presidents of @{B}QNX@{UB}. The president told that the first computers he
and  his  co-founder  bought  for the company (that was 1981) were @{B}PC@{UB}s - but the
first computers both they bought for private use at home were @{B}A1000@{UB}s!

He  told  us that he got due to the cooperation with @{B}AI@{UB} spots of coffee in their
office  -  because  when they told this to their employees and asked them who of
them  would  own  an  @{B}Amiga@{UB},  some  of  them  were  currently  standing  at  the
coffee-machine... =)

So you see we do not only have a very good Kernel-partner but even one who knows
the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  -  and  loves it and is therefore excited to cooperate with @{B}AI@{UB} for a
comeback  of  @{B}Amiga@{UB}. Corresponding were his words about @{B}Microsoft@{UB}... :) Again we
were told at the show that @{B}Amiga@{UB} will be as much ahead the competitors when it's
re-introduced as it was the first time.

@{B}QNX@{UB}  architecture  is  very  stable  (as it has to, being even used in the Space
Shuttle;  wouldn't  like to see @{B}Windows@{UB} installed there, if I were an astronaut)
and  very compact. Those who were already on their homepage may have found their
demo disk - surf the web not from HD but only from a small 1.44MB-disk. The disk
was demonstrated as well.

The new @{B}AmigaOS@{UB} microkernel will be @{B}QNX@{UB}' "@{B}Neutrino@{UB}". It is extremely modular, so
it  fits  the needs of @{B}AI@{UB}'s DC-plans: from settop-box to workstation you'll have
the  same  kernel  core  and  add  as much components as needed for the specific
device.  Something  new  in  computing  is  their  GUI "@{B}Photon@{UB}" - it's the first
microGUI. For details please look at their Homepage.

They  demonstrated  @{B}QNX@{UB} RTOS and the auditorium was impressed. Demonstrating the
abilities  of the GUI, he showed us a window not only as used from it's "front",
but  also from it's side - i.e. just a vertical line, because the window was 2D,
of course.

Then  he  demonstrated  how  a  programm running in a window on one computer was
retargeted  to another computer without any delay and easily back by clicking on
a button on the window-border for this purpose.

Also it was shown that the demo-programm was on both computers at the same time,
so  that  any  action  (for  example  mouse-movement  to  press a button in this
demo-program, a card-game) could be done from each computer.

Because  of the @{B}QNX@{UB}-architecture it is very easy to spread the tasks for example
of a Raytracer to many other computers to speed it up.

But most impressive was the following. He started @{B}Doom@{UB} in a window and moved the
window  around  while  @{B}Doom@{UB} was running without any impairments. No, this wasn't
what  I  meant to be impressive. Very impressive was what happened when he moved
the  @{B}Doom@{UB}-window to the right border of the screen: as much as it got beyond the
screenborder of the first computer, it appeared at the left border of the second
computer's screen! So he moved the window from the one computer's screen step by
step  on  the  other's one. Then he drew it back a bit, so that the left half of
the  still  running  @{B}Doom@{UB} was on the one computer's screen, the other one on the
other's.

After the conference we had half an hour to speak individually with @{I}Petro@{UI}, @{I}Jeff@{UI},
@{I}Allan@{UI} and the president of @{B}QNX@{B} (a very nice man, like the @{B}AI@{UB}-crew).

Regarding  the  Sober  Analysis-Thread  it  seems  I  were  wrong. I thought the
OS-partner  would  be  "BIG" in the meaning of well-known, rich and with certain
influence. (But the reality is much better in my opinion, too.) But now it seems
that the whole project is really something @{B}AI@{UB} has initiated, therefor I admit my
speculations  were  wrong.  Looking  at @{B}AI@{UB}, @{B}QNX@{UB} and - maybe - Transmeta, we have
three  small  companies  that fit very good together, being "BIG" in quality but
not in quantity and complementing each other.

I  did  not  ask  @{I}Jeff@{UI}  about  my former speculation regarding @{B}AI@{UB} may not be the
initiator of this project, because I talked to others before, and when I came to
@{I}Jeff@{UI} again the time was already more than over and he was already talking with a
woman  (I suppose it was his wife) about other stuff, the computers were already
removed  and  I  was  already  the  last user who was there, so I decided not to
disturb him. But looking at the facts as they are now, it's very likely this was
initiated  by  @{B}AI@{UB}, especially being aware that they were at first thinking about
another  OS-partner.  Obviously  they  heard  about  @{B}Transmeta@{UB}  (or  whoever the
@{B}MMC@{UB}-maker  is,  but  the details and the time of the patent (because it was said
they'll  tell  us  @{B}MMC@{UB}-maker's  name  around this time, i.e. in January) make it
somewhat  likely) due to their @{B}GW@{UB}-relationship and found later @{B}QNX@{UB}; as they told
due to the @{B}WOA@{UB}-announcement - maybe due to it the @{B}QNX@{UB}-Amigans heard about @{B}AI@{UB} and
their plans and contacted them then.

Instead  of  this  I  asked the @{B}QNX@{UB}-president about another topic - because they
licence  their  technology  to  many  third parties I wanted to know if it could
happen that they licence it to a competitor of @{B}AI@{UB} as well or if @{B}Amiga@{UB} would have
exclusive access to their technology.

But  now  I  notice that I didn't tell yet something about the very big question
that  rose  out  of their cooperation: Why did they cooperate with @{B}AI@{UB} instead of
doing  it all at their own since they already have a running RT-OS? What's their
benefit?  Well,  @{B}AI@{UB}'s work will mainly be to implement the APIs. As @{I}Jeff@{UI} told us
they'll  use  standard  APIs  like  OpenGL  where standards are and that they'll
implement  new  ones where necessary - there he sees a chance for @{B}AI@{UB} setting new
standards.  The @{B}QNX@{UB}-president told IMHO (I did not understand all, and the bit I
heard  had still to be translated) that the reason why they cooperate with @{B}AI@{UB} is
that  they  want  to concentrate on their kernel, while @{B}AI@{UB} has to make a full OS
out  of  it  for  the  DC-market. @{B}QNX@{UB} is small regarding employees but of a good
quality  because  they  focus on this core and care there about every detail, he
told us.

And  regarding  the  question  if  @{B}AI@{UB} has to fear competition licencing the same
technology the president told me that he could not tell me more about this topic
due  to contracts but he gave me the impression that this would not be their aim
-  their licenced partner for the market-segment of Digital Convergence is @{B}Amiga
Inc@{UB}.

All  in  all I have to say that I'm very satisfied with what I've heard and seen
at  Cologne and that I'm sure @{B}AI@{UB} do their work very well and therefore will have
a  certain  chance.  Anyway  I  doubt  very  much  that  it  will  be easy to be
successful,  because  since  the partner is no "BIG" company in the definition I
gave above it will be harder to get a foot into the markets. And, to add this, I
wouldn't  count  that much on @{B}GW@{UB}'s money regarding this. After the official part
of  the  conference  @{I}Jeff@{UI}  stressed again on the question about the relationship
@{B}GW@{UB}-@{B}AI@{UB}  that  @{B}GW@{UB}  keeps  @{B}AI@{UB} very separate; @{B}GW@{UB} does it's @{B}PC@{UB}-business, @{B}AI@{UB} does it's
@{B}Amiga@{UB}-business.

So far about my memories of the press conference. Hope I could tell some users a
little bit new.
